Berkshire Real Estate Brokerage Reports 43% Profit Decline

-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 
2011-08-05T20:50:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/berkshire-real-estate-brokerage-posts-43-profit-drop-on-refinancing-slump.html
Warren Buffett ’s  Berkshire Hathaway
Inc. (BRK/A)  said second-quarter profit at its residential real estate
brokerage dropped 43 percent on a slowdown in refinancing by
homeowners.  Net income at HomeServices of America Inc. fell by $10
million, according to a regulatory filing today from Berkshire’s
MidAmerican Energy Holdings Co., the unit that owns the
brokerage. Operating revenue at HomeServices fell 15 percent to
$290 million, MidAmerican said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Frye in New York at 
 afrye@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  